content: My monthly income after taxes is around $4,500. My fixed necessary expenses include $1,800 for rent, $500 for car payment, $150 for insurance premiums, and $100 for internet and phone bills. My minimum debt payments are $500 for credit cards and $300 for student loans. I usually spend around $800 on dining out and entertainment, $200 on hobbies, and $300 on personal spending like clothing and beauty products. I'd like to allocate around $500 for luxury purchases, and my savings goals include building an emergency fund and saving for retirement.
